^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Nicely played. Let us discuss cp's 1 diamond opener, as that is an interesting treatment. Many people play that even with 4 diamonds and 5 clubs, you open 1 diamond, because you have an easy rebid of 2 clubs. They feel that if you open 1@C, and are not strong enough to reverse to 2@D, they don't wish to bid 2@C over 1 of a major by partner. Although that is a fairly common treatment, I don't particularly care for it. Because now if partner opens 1@D and rebids 2@C, I don't know if she has 5 diamonds and 4 clubs, or 4 diamonds and 5 clubs. And with equal length in the minors and a weak hand, it is not clear whether to correct to diamonds or pass 2@C.|
