^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|pam has an interesting dilemma. She has several choices of bids, all of which have merit. She can bid 1@S as she did, or she can bid 2@C, or  she can choose to double and correct to clubs. The problem with bidding 2@C or doubling and correcting is you might lose the spade suit. So 1@S could work out well as it did. My 3@S bid is preemptive, showing 4 spades and less than a limit raise. That makes pam's hand incredibly good. Using Bergen hand evaluation she has 15 HCP plus 1 for quality suit and 3 length points so 19 Starting Points. Additionally, once I raise spades, she adds 4 for 2 singletons, plus another point for club side suit, so 24 total Bergen Points. |
