NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|If I have KQ of spades and five points slam is on a finesse. If I have K of clubs or ace of diamonds as well, slam makes. But those are very specific cards, so 4@S is probably best. The point is, pam's hand is worth 24 Bergen Points, meaning with 9 Bergen Points in my hand, slam is quite possible. So, even though I bid 3@S, there was a small chance we had slam, but not worth exploring. One more comment on the bidding. I don't think west has an opening bid. even by traditional point count, does not meet the rule of 20. And using Bergens' methods, Starting Points are 11 HCP - 1 for dubious doubleton, so only 10 Bergen starting points.|
