NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now, one comment on the play. It turns out spades are 2-2. Once West plays a spade honor, it turns out pam should finesse east for the other spade honor. That is known as "the law of restricted choice", and it is 75% that ally has the other spade honor. Unfortunately, on this hand, the 25% probability kicked in, but in general, missing the QJ, if you see one of them drop, you should play the other opponent for the other honor.|
