^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|There is a general declarer principle which ally should have followed to make her life easier
generally speaking, when cashing a suit, you should play the honors in the shorter hand first, to avoid blocking problems. So in the first trick, ally should play the ace, to avoid blocking clubs. Similarly, on the spades, ally should play the AQ first, to avoid blocking the spades. These plays will not cost you the contract. It turns out if she does that, because of all the good breaks she makes six.|
